The Washington Post revealed poor treatment of wounded soldiers at Walter Reed, sparking investigations and outrage.
Democratic Senator Barack Obama called for top-notch care for veterans.
Defense Secretary Robert Gates appointed a panel to review conditions at Walter Reed and the National Naval Medical Center.
Army officials faced criticism for neglecting soldiers' well-being and bureaucratic inefficiencies.
Rep. Tom Davis condemned the Army's long-standing knowledge of issues at Walter Reed.
The Army pledged to address substandard living conditions and streamline medical evaluations.
Gates promised swift improvements and accountability for the unacceptable situation.
The independent review panel will assess rehabilitative care at both facilities.
